config PARAM_STORE
	bool "Flash-backed parameter store"
	default n
	depends on ARCH_HAVE_PROGMEM
	---help---
		Enables the param_store library, providing a ping-pong flash
		parameter store with a heap-allocated RAM scratch buffer.

		Parameters are stored in two equally-sized flash sectors. On
		each save, the inactive sector is erased and written, then
		becomes the new active sector. This guarantees the previous
		parameter set survives a power loss during a write.

		The user defines the parameter data structure. Only its size
		is relevant to the library. Access is through lock()/unlock()
		for RAM access and save()/reset() for flash persistence.

if PARAM_STORE

config PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_A_ADDR
	hex "Base address of parameter sector A"
	default 0x0800F800
	---help---
		Flash address of the first parameter sector.

		Both sectors must be independently erasable — they must not
		share an erase block with code or data sections.

		STM32F103 64K: last two 1K pages are 0x0800F800 / 0x0800FC00.

		Must be aligned to CONFIG_PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_SIZE and reserved
		in the linker script to prevent the toolchain from placing code
		or data here.

config PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_B_ADDR
	hex "Base address of parameter sector B"
	default 0x0800FC00
	---help---
		Flash address of the second parameter sector.
		Must be aligned to CONFIG_PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_SIZE and must not
		overlap with sector A or any code/data section.

config PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_SIZE
	int "Flash sector (erase page) size in bytes"
	default 1024
	---help---
		Must match the erase granularity of the target device:

		  STM32F1 low/medium density      1024
		  STM32F1 high density            2048
		  STM32F4 sectors 0-3            16384
		  STM32F4 sector 4              65536
		  STM32F4 sectors 5-11         131072

		Both sectors A and B must be this exact size. The maximum
		parameter data payload is (PARAM_STORE_SECTOR_SIZE - 12).

config PARAM_STORE_MAGIC
	hex "Magic word written to each valid sector header"
	default 0xDEADCAFE
	---help---
		A sector is considered valid only if it starts with this 32-bit
		word. Change this value whenever the parameter struct is modified
		in a backward-incompatible way — existing flash content with the
		old magic will be treated as blank, triggering a first-boot
		re-initialisation from defaults.

endif # PARAM_STORE
